<p>fateful hours.  Now, although it is still semi open warfare, there is order &amp; the shelling is more or less regular; but for a day &amp; a night, with German rifles &amp; machine guns bunking in farm houses &amp; [indecipherable] sweeping the half back areas such as that between Castre &amp; Fletre, it must have been terrible.  Not to mention the bloody &amp; sweating battles fought out in the high green fields of crops, with hedges as cover.</p>
